# Chatwoot Project Structure

Chatwoot is an open-source customer support platform built with Ruby on Rails and Vue.js. This rule outlines the project structure and important files/folders.

## Root Directory Structure

```
chatwoot/
├── app/                       # Main application code (Rails MVC + Vue.js)
├── config/                    # Application configuration
├── db/                        # Database migrations and schema
├── lib/                       # Custom libraries and modules
├── spec/                      # Test specifications (RSpec)
├── public/                    # Static assets and compiled files
├── enterprise/                # Enterprise edition features
├── deployment/                # Deployment scripts and configurations
├── swagger/                   # API documentation
├── docker/                    # Docker configuration files
├── theme/                     # Theme configuration (colors, icons)
├── .cursor/                   # Cursor IDE configuration
├── .github/                   # GitHub workflows and templates
├── .vscode/                   # VS Code configuration
└── ...                        # Configuration files
```

## Core Application Structure (`app/`)

### Backend Rails Structure
```
app/
├── controllers/               # API and web controllers
├── models/                    # ActiveRecord models
├── services/                  # Business logic services
├── workers/                   # Background job workers
├── jobs/                      # ActiveJob classes
├── mailers/                   # Email handling
├── mailboxes/                 # ActionMailbox handlers
├── channels/                  # ActionCable channels
├── policies/                  # Authorization policies
├── presenters/                # View layer helpers
├── builders/                  # Object builders
├── finders/                   # Query objects
├── listeners/                 # Event listeners
├── dispatchers/               # Event dispatchers
├── actions/                   # Action objects
├── drops/                     # Liquid template drops
├── dashboards/                # Admin dashboard configuration
├── fields/                    # Form field objects
├── helpers/                   # View helpers
├── views/                     # Server-side templates
└── assets/                    # Rails assets
```

### Frontend Vue.js Structure
```
app/javascript/
├── dashboard/                 # Main dashboard application
│   ├── App.vue               # Root Vue component
│   ├── components/           # Vue components
│   ├── components-next/      # Next-generation components
│   ├── routes/              # Vue router configuration
│   ├── store/               # Vuex store modules
│   ├── api/                 # API client modules
│   ├── mixins/              # Vue mixins
│   ├── modules/             # Feature modules
│   ├── i18n/                # Internationalization
│   ├── assets/              # Frontend assets
│   ├── composables/         # Vue composition API
│   ├── constants/           # JavaScript constants
│   └── helper/              # Helper functions
├── portal/                   # Customer portal
├── widget/                   # Embeddable chat widget
├── sdk/                      # JavaScript SDK
├── survey/                   # Survey functionality
├── v3/                       # API v3 related code
├── shared/                   # Shared components/utilities
├── superadmin_pages/         # Super admin interface
├── design-system/            # Design system components
├── entrypoints/              # Vite entry points
└── histoire.setup.ts         # Storybook/Histoire setup
```

## Configuration (`config/`)

### Key Configuration Files
```
config/
├── application.rb             # Main Rails application config
├── routes.rb                  # Application routes
├── database.yml              # Database configuration
├── environments/             # Environment-specific configs
├── initializers/             # Rails initializers
├── locales/                  # I18n translation files
├── languages/                # Language configurations
├── integration/              # Third-party integrations
├── features.yml              # Feature flags
├── installation_config.yml   # Installation configuration
├── vite.json                 # Vite configuration
├── puma.rb                   # Puma web server config
├── sidekiq.yml               # Background job configuration
├── schedule.yml              # Cron job scheduling
├── storage.yml               # Active Storage configuration
└── secrets.yml               # Application secrets
```

## Database (`db/`)

```
db/
├── migrate/                   # Database migrations
├── schema.rb                 # Current database schema
└── seeds.rb                  # Database seed data
```

## Custom Libraries (`lib/`)

### Important Library Files
```
lib/
├── chatwoot_app.rb           # Main application class
├── chatwoot_hub.rb           # Hub functionality
├── global_config.rb          # Global configuration
├── events/                   # Event handling
├── integrations/             # Third-party integrations
├── webhooks/                 # Webhook handlers
├── tasks/                    # Rake tasks
├── seeders/                  # Database seeders
├── redis/                    # Redis utilities
├── filters/                  # Data filters
├── custom_exceptions/        # Custom exception classes
├── assets/                   # Asset handling
└── linear/                   # Linear integration
```

## Testing (`spec/`)

### Test Organization
```
spec/
├── models/                   # Model tests
├── controllers/              # Controller tests
├── services/                 # Service tests
├── workers/                  # Worker tests
├── jobs/                     # Job tests
├── requests/                 # Request tests
├── integration/              # Integration tests
├── factories/                # Test factories
├── fixtures/                 # Test fixtures
├── support/                  # Test support files
├── rails_helper.rb           # Rails test configuration
├── spec_helper.rb            # RSpec configuration
└── test_helper.rb            # Test helper
```

## Enterprise Features (`enterprise/`)

```
enterprise/
├── app/                      # Enterprise-specific code
├── config/                   # Enterprise configuration
├── lib/                      # Enterprise libraries
└── LICENSE                   # Enterprise license
```

## Static Assets (`public/`)

```
public/
├── assets/                   # Compiled assets
├── brand-assets/             # Brand assets
├── dashboard/                # Dashboard static files
├── integrations/             # Integration assets
├── downloads/                # Downloadable files
├── audio/                    # Audio files
├── favicon-*.png             # Favicon files
├── manifest.json             # Web app manifest
├── robots.txt                # Search engine robots
├── sw.js                     # Service worker
└── *.html                    # Error pages (404, 500, etc.)
```

## Deployment & DevOps

### Deployment Files
```
deployment/
├── setup_20.04.sh            # Ubuntu 20.04 setup script
├── setup_18.04.sh            # Ubuntu 18.04 setup script
├── nginx_chatwoot.conf       # Nginx configuration
├── chatwoot-*.service        # Systemd service files
├── chatwoot.target           # Systemd target
└── chatwoot                  # Service script
```

### Docker Configuration
```
docker/
└── (Docker-related files)

# Root Docker files
docker-compose.yaml           # Development Docker setup
docker-compose.production.yaml # Production Docker setup
docker-compose.test.yaml      # Test Docker setup
Dockerfile                    # (if present)
.dockerignore                 # Docker ignore patterns
```

## Configuration Files (Root)

### Development & Build
- `package.json` - Node.js dependencies and scripts
- `pnpm-lock.yaml` - Package manager lock file
- `vite.config.ts` - Vite build configuration
- `tailwind.config.js` - TailwindCSS configuration
- `postcss.config.js` - PostCSS configuration
- `histoire.config.ts` - Histoire (Storybook) configuration
- `vitest.setup.js` - Vitest test configuration

### Ruby & Rails
- `Gemfile` - Ruby gem dependencies
- `Gemfile.lock` - Ruby gem lock file
- `Rakefile` - Rake tasks
- `config.ru` - Rack configuration
- `Capfile` - Capistrano deployment
- `Procfile*` - Process definitions for deployment

### Code Quality & CI/CD
- `.eslintrc.js` - ESLint configuration
- `.rubocop.yml` - RuboCop Ruby linter
- `.prettierrc` - Prettier code formatter
- `.scss-lint.yml` - SCSS linting
- `.rspec` - RSpec configuration
- `.circleci/` - CircleCI configuration
- `.github/` - GitHub Actions workflows

### Theme & Design
```
theme/
├── colors.js                 # Color palette definitions
└── icons.js                  # Icon definitions
```

## API Documentation (`swagger/`)

```
swagger/
├── swagger.json              # OpenAPI specification
├── index.yml                 # Swagger index
├── index.html                # Swagger UI
├── paths/                    # API endpoint definitions
├── definitions/              # API model definitions
├── parameters/               # API parameter definitions
└── tag_groups/               # API tag groupings
```

## Development Guidelines

### File Organization Principles
1. **MVC Pattern**: Follow Rails MVC structure for backend
2. **Component-Based**: Use Vue.js components for frontend
3. **Feature Modules**: Organize by feature in `modules/`
4. **Shared Code**: Common utilities in `shared/`
5. **Enterprise Separation**: Keep enterprise features isolated

### Important File Naming
- Ruby files: `snake_case.rb`
- Vue components: `PascalCase.vue`
- JavaScript: `camelCase.js`
- Stylesheets: `kebab-case.scss`
- Test files: `*_spec.rb` for RSpec

### Key Entry Points
- **Main App**: `app/javascript/dashboard/App.vue`
- **Widget**: `app/javascript/widget/`
- **API**: `config/routes.rb`
- **Background Jobs**: `app/workers/`
- **Database**: `db/schema.rb`

### Development Environment
- **Frontend**: Vite (configured in `vite.config.ts`)
- **Backend**: Rails (configured in `config/application.rb`)
- **Database**: PostgreSQL (configured in `config/database.yml`)
- **Cache**: Redis (configured in `config/redis.yml`)
- **Jobs**: Sidekiq (configured in `config/sidekiq.yml`)

This structure supports a modern, scalable customer support platform with clear separation of concerns and modular architecture.
